title: Asper and Piol Become Friends
description: Asper and Piol's families were close, they grew up together.

title: Asper and Piol Become a Couple
description: After the death of Piol's father, the two become very close and begin a romantic relationship.

title: Asper and Piol Move to Vauban Station
description: Piol and Asper move to Vauban Station so that they can work on Project ACSR.

title: Project ACSR
description: A project for creating the perfect 'immune' system.

title: Castus and Octavia Start Project ACSR
description: Pressured by the public, this project (and others) were started to fight the outbreak on Argos V.

title: Castus Becomes Obsessed
description: Castus becomes pressured by the public, stresses himself out, and takes it out on Octavia, he is always working on the project and pushes Octavia to work an unhealthy amount also.

title: Octavia Leaves Castus and Project ACSR
description: Octavia breaks up with Castus and leaves the project due to his obsession.

title: Castus Recruits New Members
description: He looks for more members so he can be less stressed with the project, he also needs to fill Octavia's position.

title: Asper and Piol Join Project ACSR
description: Both were looking for a project to join. Piol joins due to it's connection to his father's death from the outbreak on Argos V.

title: Bunal Station Deep Space Survey
description: Humanity still hasn't found signs of any other intelligent life, this station is dedicated to this search

title: Ruins Discovered
description: Probes come across the ruins and the data is transmitted to Bunal Station.

title: Learn of the Artifact
description: Data received from the probes is analysed, they learn of the artifact but do not know much.

title: Shard Locations Calculated
description: They deduce that the artifact was split and the shards were propelled into space when the planet was destroyed, they then calculate their trajectories.

title: Vale
description: A short description...

title: Artifact Recovery Mission
description: A mission to recover and research the artifact. At this time, little is known about the artifact but they know it's powerful.

title: Commander Hidraa Notified
description: Admiral Furen Hidraa tasks his son (Commander Roden Furen Hidraa) to lead a mission to recover and research the artifact.

title: New Century Celebration
description: The inhabitants of Vauban Station celebrate the start of the 26th century.

title: Crew Briefed On Cover Mission
description: The crew are briefed on a mission to study the star of the Kalor system, this is a cover for the real mission.

title: Begin Trip To The Kalor System
description: The Avaritia, Discivolo, and Pelavita begin travelling to the Kalor System.

title: Select Crew Briefed On Real Mission
description: Select senior crew are notified about the mission to recover and research the Artifact.

title: Ships Gathered
description: Ships are gathered and prepped for the mission.

title: Earth Government Alliance
description: From what was formally USA, UK, Japan, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, and the Pacific Islands

title: Space War
description: War between the E.G.A. and F.S.R. over space

title: Federation of Soviet Republics
description: A Soviet Alliance is born after a resurrection due to technological discovery and new dominance over space

title: Fenrir Station Built
description: Built as a military training and education base

title: Vauban Station Built
description: Built for ship building and research due to it's proximity to large amounts of resources

title: Avaritia Built
description: Vauban Station's main ship. Regularly retrofitted with new technology

title: Novictus Built
description:
Built by the F.S.R. as a warship.
Means "New Victory"

title: Sotalis Settled
description: Likely settled by the F.S.R. early on, possibly the first self-sustaining colony developed

title: Open Government Initiative Begins
description: Starts as a civil movement, turns scientific

title: E.G.A Joins
description: Initiatives to merge begin after the movement gains traction and proves effective on it's own, starting as a simple government

title: F.S.R. Retreats to Sotalis
description: Rejecting the offer to join the O.G.A, they continue fighting and are forced to retreat to their capital planet

title: Kalor III Expedition
description: The F.S.R. needs more resources, sends expedition here

title: Novictus Repurposed
description: The Novictus is repurposed for this mission

title: 'Skit' Prototype Given to Piol
description: Finished shortly after Piol's father's death, given to Piol for emotional support

title: Arrives at Kalor III
description:
After a long journey, (outdated WarpPoint drives)
the Novictus arrives in orbit of Kalor III

title: Cohen Heads Colony Construction
description: Chief Engineer Cohen Nuro leads the construction of the colony, he knows the ins and outs of the entire colony

title: Asper and Piol Born
description: Asper Pectal and Piol Deltos are born on, and grow up on Fenrir Station.

title: Fenrir Station Rehaul
description: The station becomes less militaristic, is retrofitted, and the entire education system is updated

title: Vauban Station Rehaul
description: The station doesn't physically change, but its system of governing changes

title: Bunal Station Constructed
description:
Bunal Station is created sometime after the O.G.A. is formed.
It uses cutting edge tech for deep space surveying with probes

title: Lenus Anim
description: Grew up on Sotalis, during the end of the war

title: Joins Mission with His Father
description: Without work and desperate, Lenus and Murtou join the expedition to mine

title: Leave for Kalor III
description: After preparations are done, the Novictus leaves for Kalor III

title: Construction Ends
description: Planned construction ends, repairs and extensions are still happening of course

title: Mining Begins
description: Mining is now fully facilitated and ready to start

title: Returns Deminish
description: Things don't go too well and the colony begins to lose resources instead of gaining them

title: Concerns Begin with Small Incidents
description: Workers get overworked trying to get enough resources to stay afloat, fatigue causes small mistakes and injuries

title: First Lethal Incident
description: Murtou Anim is injured, and some are killed in an incident

title: Octavia Rejoins Project ACSR
description: After the situation improved, she joined back, but did not get back together with Castus

title: Project RAINNER
description: AI Project created from declassified tech used for non-military applications

title: Some Tech Declassified / Repurposed Projects
description: Following the new alliance, some tech is declassified and shared, allowing a boom in research and technology

title: Discivolo and Pelavita Constructed
description: These ships were likely constructed after the war was over, but it's possible they were created late in the war

title: Miner Strikes Begin
description: The hostile work conditions cause the miners to be the first to strike

title: Melk's Movement
description: Melk's following from the miner strikes to the birth of the corrupt

title: Melk Sent to Negotiate
description: Head Counsellor Erra Melk is sent to liaison and negotiate with the strikers

title: Lenus Joins Melk
description: Lenus has enough and joins the strike also, leading him to join Melk's cause

title: Situation Escalates
description: More incidents and death result from less workers and therefore less resources, more energy restrictions and more cuts

title: Negotiation Hits a Dead-end
description: Gov won't back down because they need resources to stay alive; Citizens won't back down because of overworking and physically hostile conditions.

title: Melk Stresses, Hatches a Plan
description: His supporters convince him that he would make a good leader, he decides that the only way to get out of the dead-end is to swap out the Gov.

title: Melk Overthrows The Gov
description: With the help of his many supporters (some within the Gov), Melk fairly easily overthrows the Government

title: Melk Assembles a Council
description: Also known as "Melk's Circle" or "Melk's Inner Circle"

title: Fleet Arrives at Edge of Kalor System
description: Stays near the edge because this is where the Artifact shard will pass

title: Spread Lies to Survive
description: Afraid of his own followers, (who have become violent and uncontrollable) they begin to lie to keep them on their side, not wanting to risk the irrational mob killing them to take charge.

title: Gets Worse Without Proper Gov
description: The situation gets even worse without the experience, protocols, and work by the old gov

title: Send Probes To Study Kalor Star
description: Probes are sent to study the star, as they won't have enough warning if the ships are near the star; Also a good excuse to stay near the intercept point.

title: Discover Colony on Kalor III
description: Sensor readings from ships and probes confirm the presence of an illegal colony on Kalor III, they promptly send a report entry to the O.G.A.

title: Avaritia Moves to Investigate
description: The Avaritia moves, assessing the threat in an attempt to protect the Discivolo in case of hijacking attempt.

title: 'Away Team' Sent to Kalor III
description: Kimiko (First Officer) and Borel (Chief Security) are sent to establish contact

title: Aid Is Given By The Avaritia
description: Logistic and Medical teams are sent to the planet along with possible resources to aid the colony

title: Supernova Event
description: Kalor star becomes a supernova, releasing destructive energy throughout the Kalor System

title: Probes Detect, All Alerted
description: Since the probes can send FTL messages, they are warned several minutes before the radiation will be intercepted.

title: Shuttles + Pelavita Lead Evacuation
description: Shuttles from the Novictus and the Avaritia are sent to pick up colonists as well as the Pelavita.

title: EMP Devastates Infrastructure
description:
The energy released from the supernova disrupts remaining tech on Kalor III.
Causing life support to be ruined, even atmosphere protects against radiation from the blast

title: Most Taken, Few Left Behind
description: Within the approx 8-10 minute escape window, some people are left behind

title: Post-war
description: Description of this era

title: Melk Meets with the Liasons
description:
As new leader, Melk meets and corresponds with the away team.
He explains the situation

title: Raised by Mother, till ~4
description: While his father fights in the war, Lenus is brought up on Sotalis with his mother

title: Lenus' Father Returns
description: Following the war, his father returns home

title: Becomes the O.G.A.
description: The Open Government Alliance is formed after many successes and independent planetary governments join

title: Mother Leaves
description: She leaves after she learns that Murtou is having an affair + everything else going on

title: Piol's Father is Laid Off
description: Piol's father is laid off following changes at Fenrir Station

title: Gan Retires
description: Gan retires to live his dream of being an explorer, now charting Argos V

title: Argos V Outbreak
description: An outbreak of infections from a particularly nasty strain of carcinogenic bacteria that mainly effects mitochondria

title: Infection Cured, But Not Cancer
description: Gan's bacterial infection is cured, but the mitochondrial cancer remains and is uncurable

title: Gan Infected
description: Gan is infected, begins having symptoms related to low energy levels in cells

title: Asper Joins the Deltos' for Gan's Last Trip
description: Gan takes his family and friends on a sightseeing adventure of the galaxy to enjoy his final months

title: Asper Starts Making 'Skit'
description: She begins to create an emotional support device, inspired by the situation

title: Gan Passes Away
description: Gan's condition deteriorated and passed away near the end of the trip

title: Leave Kalor System
description: The Novictus, Avaritia, and Pelavita meet up with the Discivolo, and leave the system

title: Complex A.I. Ban Lifted
description: Ban against complex A.I. is lifted following the war

title: Asper Joins, Starts as Low-Level Employee
description: Due to her low experience in the field, she begins as a junior, eventually rises the ranks as a fast and motivated learner

title: Waypoint Construction Begins
description: In order for humans to directly access and research the ruins, probes are sent to automatically construct a waypoint station

description: The Avaritia picks up the artifact shard after 'accidentally' finding it

title: RAINNER Establishes Communication with Shard
description: In an experimental move, RAINNER is connected to the shard in order to try and teach it English and about humanity in a much shorter time than manual work would

title: Ex-Colonists Accommodated
description: Spread across the Novictus, Pelavita, Avaritia, and Discivolo

description: Melk becomes suspicious of the item retrieved and the complete restriction of the Discivolo, digs deeper

title: Supernova
description:
A supernova is a star that suddenly increases in brightness because it is running out of fuel.
It then explodes, sending out a huge amount of energy and matter.

title: Argos V
description:
A habitable planet that was fought over in the Space War.
It was eventually claimed and settled by the Earth Government Alliance following the war.

This was the site of the Argos V Outbreak.

title: Kalor System
description:
A system in the Milky Way Galaxy.
It contains the planet Kalor III.

title: Earth
description:
The planet that humans originated from.
It is the capital planet of the Earth Government Alliance.

title: Human
description:
An intelligent species that originated from Earth.
They are the dominant species in the mostly lifeless Milky Way Galaxy.

title: WarpPoint Drive
description:
A type of drive that allows a ship to travel at faster-than-light speeds.
It can reach speeds of ~25C for the average ship.

title: Waypoint Station
description: Strategically placed in orbit of a star, these stations can transport signals and ships to other connected Waypoint Stations almost instantly.

title: Gravity Panel
description:
A device that can generate a linear gravitational field by bending space-time.
It is used to create artificial gravity.

title: Force Field
description:
A force field created by bending space-time.
It is used in shuttle bays to keep air in while also allowing more massive objects to pass through.
